If we want to access only one behaviour of an object only once,
then we will create Ananamous object.
Example:

public class Car {
   String brand;
   String color;
   int cost;
   
   void allowToDrive()
   {
      System.out.println("Car is moving.....");
   }
}

public class CarApp {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
       new Car().allowToDrive();
       new Car().allowToDrive();
   }
}

Output: Car is moving.....
        Car is moving.....